--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 1. When you see DoZ fighting someone, be it MiM, BSK or The Curse, feel free to heal whoever is about to die or teleport them or mezz DoZ member or manaburn DoZ member. When you are sent a tell &quot;please stay out of the fight, this is DoZ guildwar and it doesn't concern you&quot; reply as rudely as possible that you dont give a damn, reserve for yourself right to heal/mezz anyone you damn please. At that point, it is advisable that you also add &quot;at any rate you guys are no better than random PKers&quot; even if you are healing The Curse member that is fighting DoZ. When contacted shortly after the incident and informed that you and/or your guild are KoS to DoZ, reply with &quot;as if you lamers dare to KoS us&quot;, proceed to taunt and insult DoZ officer, tell them their guild's days are numbered and swear you will dedicate your EQ days to hunting DoZ down and owning them singlehandedly.<br>
<br>
2. Feel free to read DoZ KoS list and open invite people from it into your guild. Make sure abovementioned members openly taunt DoZ while wearing your tag, reminding them all the loots they whored/stole or other events that could have been reason to be put on DoZ KoS list. Make sure when informed that abovementioned person is indeed KoS to DoZ you say &quot;so what u gonna do about huh?&quot; and tell DoZ officer to shove it. If you find DoZ request for off kos to be reasonable or even mild, make sure you go to nonpvp zone like PoTranqulity and start mouthing DoZ off. Then proceed attacking DoZ members (note, not the pvpers) and try to train/exp loss them so DoZ feels the pain. (Hey SG, that worked, didn't it?)<br>
<br>
3. There is freedom of speech and if anyone tells you that your inalienable right to say what you want is violated, make sure u tell that person to @#%$ themselves, then tell them to @#%$ themselves some more. Thus if you arent in range to DoZ, you can already be working towards ultimate goal of your guild's career (and your own) getting yourselves KoS to DoZ. That is accomplished by sitting all day in PoTranq or PoK (or pvp zone if you are out of range) and running your mouth. It especially works well when say DoZ helped your guild with something just a few days prior. Say you were doing Prince in Chardok and your newbie guild wiped.. and your ench. really wants the epic.. and Sadko helped you do the prince.. actually more like soloed it... make sure a newbie from your guild goes to say PoV the next day and starts /oocing that Sadko is a PK and DoZ needs to be KoSed off the server. What may have not pissed Sadko from someone he doesn't know, is sure to piss him off when he HELPED you just the day before and THEN you mouth him off. So be creative!<br>
<br>
Those are just 3 sure ways to get on our KoS list. There are many more that you and your guild can try and do. So far those worked just fine for BSK, Reverant, NVS and SG. Currently DoZ considering peace with SG and Reverant so there are vacant spots on our KoS motd, and YOU AND YOUR GUILD CAN BE ON IT! Start working for those TODAY! <br>
